How to Run the Project
Using Eclipse
Open Eclipse.
Select File → Open Projects from File System.
Choose the project folder:
YorkURoomScheduler
Open:
src/scheduler/Main.java
Right-click Main.java.
Select Run As → Java Application.

The Java Swing application window should open.

Using VS Code
Open the project folder in VS Code.
Make sure the Java Extension Pack is installed.
Open:
src/scheduler/Main.java
Click Run above the main method, or run from the terminal if Java is configured.


